# Architecture Diagram Maintenance

`docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` is the source-of-truth system diagram. Update it whenever you make structural changes.

## Update triggers

| Change | Diagrams to update |
|--------|-------------------|
| New app or package | §1 System Overview, §2 Package Graph |
| New API route | §1 System Overview (add to API node) |
| New agent | §5 Agent Roster |
| New ingestion job or schedule change | §4 Ingestion Pipeline |
| New DB model or relation | §6 DB Models |
| New external service or connector | §1 System Overview |
| Deployment cost or platform change | §7 Deployment table |

## Rules

- Update the `Last updated` date at the top of the file on every edit.
- Do not rewrite unrelated diagrams when making a focused change.
- Keep node labels short — one line of context max.
- New agents go in the correct subgraph (`Live`, `Planned`) in §5.
- New ingestion jobs must include their schedule in the node label in §4.
